  "prompt": "Why did Quora remove the 'needs improvement' tags?",
  "response": "Quora removed the \"needs improvement\" tags as part of its ongoing efforts to streamline the user experience and encourage more positive engagement on the platform. The company likely found that these tags were not as effective as intended in fostering high-quality content or in encouraging users to improve their contributions. Instead, Quora may be focusing on other strategies to maintain quality, such as improving content moderation tools, enhancing algorithms to surface better content, and relying more on community-driven feedback and upvotes to highlight valuable contributions. This change is in line with broader trends in social media and online communities where platforms seek to maintain a positive atmosphere and reduce potentially negative or discouraging signals.",
